mods.abstract: Page 123 of the album includes four photographs.; Photograph 1 [1] shows four men loading cauliflower in produce crates.; Photograph 2 [2] shows rows of cauliflower in a field while four men pack harvested cauliflower in produce crates.; Photograph 3 [3] shows four men packing cauliflower in produce crates in a field. Stacks of packed crates shown on the right in foreground.; Photograph 4 [4] shows five men packing cauliflower in produce crates in a field.; Most crates in Photos 1-4 are printed with "Grown in Louisiana / Louisiana Distributing Co. Thibodaux, LA" or "Grown by Claiborne Co. / White Castle, LA".
mods.note: Compare Photographs 1-4 to the following publication. G.L. (1913, May) Preliminary Report on Winter Cauliflower. Louisiana Bulletin, No. 140, p. 13. Photograph caption reads, "Crates of Cauliflower."; Also compare photographs to additional publication. Wilkinson J.W. (1916, July) December Cauliflower. The country gentleman, Vol. 81 (No. 28), p. 9.
